His time at Arsenal began at nine years old, he spent four years at the club before being released 😢

Marcus Rashford didn't hold back when it came to identifying Manchester United's problems 😬

Speaking to The Rest is Football Podcast, Rashford made his feeling clear on the current state of his beloved club 🗣️

“This is where I speak about being realistic about what your situation is. We’ve had that many different managers, ideas and strategies in order to win that you end up in no man’s land."

"Any team that has been successful over a period of time has principles that mean that any coach or player that comes in has to align to or add to the principles."

"At times, United were hungry to win but it was reactionary. If your direction is always changing you can’t expect to win the league.”

alt: Photo by GOAL on August 07, 2025. May be an image of 5 people, people playing football, people playing soccer, stadium and text.
caption:
Como v Real Betis was anything but a friendly match 😬

Tensions started to rise when Como were 2-0 up, with Betis goalkeeper Alvaro Valles leaving his penalty area to try and get the ball off one of the Italian side's players to take a free-kick 😅

Things started to get messy after that, as Pablo Fornals and Massimo Perrone came to blows... Fornals landed the first hit in the face of Perrone, who naturally swung back in his defence 🥊

Things got so out of hand that Betis forward Cucho Hernandez accidentally punched his own teammate Natan whilst appearing to aim for Perrone, but missed 💀

Somehow, Fornals managed to escape without a red card. Both Perrone and Hector Bellerin received straight red cards 🤯

All this in a friendly match 😅

Curtis Jones picks between the Premier League’s finest, past vs present ⚔️ @adidasfootball @liverpoolfc

It’s not every day you get a 10/10 rating from L’Equipe 👏

Desire Doue became just the 17th player to receive the perfect score following his Champions League final masterclass against Inter 🏆

France Under-21 duo Franck Sauzee and Bruno Martini were the first to score a perfect 10/10 back in 1988, followed by Russia striker Oleg Salenko, who scored five goals against Cameroon at the 1994 World Cup 🤯

Aarhus goalkeeper Lars Windfeld was next on the honours board after his display against Nantes in the 1997 UEFA Cup, but since 2000 only 15 more players have been awarded a 10/10 rating by L’Equipe 😳

alt: Photo by GOAL on May 07, 2025.
caption:
Simone Inzaghi is a truly magnificent manager 💙

Record signing Benjamin Pavard joined from Bayern Munich for a reported £26m, with match-winning midfielder Davide Frattesi costing around £20m from Sassuolo 🤝

While the incomings have been frugal, Inzaghi has had to deal with losing the likes of Romelu Lukaku, Achraf Hakimi, Andre Onana and Marcelo Brozovic 😩

But Inzaghi's ability to work with the tools he's got and extract the very best out of every player in his squad has seen Inter thrive under his leadership 👏
